snippet.title: The new Facebook Home ad, complete with drag queen
snippet.description: Facebook releases the launch ad for its new attempt to take over your Android phone. Here, Home takes over an airplane, with some interesting characters.

snippet.title: Aviate Beta (Android)
snippet.description: Yahoo-owned Android launcher Aviate groups your apps into collections and show them to you when the time (or location) is right.

snippet.title: No homecoming queen vote if you don't wear RFID tag?
snippet.description: San Antonio schools have become very enthusiastic about RFID tagging students. One student reportedly claims to have been told "No tag. No vote for homecoming king and queen."

snippet.title: YouTube quitter offered job by Queen Latifah
snippet.description: In an interview on Queen Latifah's talk show, Marina Shifrin is offered a rather good job by the Queen. Friday, it might be revealed whether she accepts.

snippet.title: The queen: On Facebook, but not your friend
snippet.description: Queen Elizabeth II, a personage of renowned tech-forward proclivities, joins Facebook. But you will not be able to befriend her.

snippet.title: Internet pioneers to collect first Queen Elizabeth Prizes
snippet.description: The queen of England will award the trophies Wednesday for a new million-pound prize to encourage engineering to Tim Berners-Lee, Robert Kahn, Vint Cerf, Marc Andreessen, and Louis Pouzin.

snippet.title: When droids break their huddle
snippet.description: Road Trip 2010: After a mass gathering of droids--R2-D2s and friends--at Celebration V, what happens when they must all go their separate ways? A lot of beeping, booping, and confusion over whose R2 is whose.

snippet.title: Acer T272HUL
snippet.description: The only thing cooler than a monitor with a million colors is a monitor with a billion colors, and Acer is offering both.
